---
import "../styles/global.css";
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>blueForge documentation</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="User-facing documentation for blueForge: Smith, Apprentice, verification, and receipts."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="top">
      <a class="brand" href="/">blueForge docs</a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/getting-started/install">Get started</a>
        <a href="/concepts/smith-and-apprentice">Concepts</a>
        <a href="/how-to/set-up-providers">How-to</a>
        <a href="/reference/glossary">Glossary</a>
        <a href="https://mobluehq-status.pages.dev">System status</a>
      </nav>
    </header>
    <div class="landing">
      <h1>Welcome to blueForge</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        blueForge is the MOBLUEHQ desktop environment for model-assisted development:
        a chat surface (Smith), a coding agent (Apprentice), and receipts that show what ran.
      </p>
      <div class="grid" style="margin-top:2rem">
        <a class="card" href="/getting-started/install" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
          <strong>Install</strong>
          <p class="muted" style="margin:0.5rem 0 0">Get the app running on your machine.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/concepts/smith-and-apprentice" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
          <strong>Smith and Apprentice</strong>
          <p class="muted" style="margin:0.5rem 0 0">Names for the chat panel and the agent.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/how-to/set-up-providers" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
          <strong>Set up providers</strong>
          <p class="muted" style="margin:0.5rem 0 0">Connect the models you already pay for.</p>
        </a>
        <a class="card" href="/how-to/report-bugs" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
          <strong>Report a problem</strong>
          <p class="muted" style="margin:0.5rem 0 0">Use the in-app Report button and public status.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
